olive oil
1 stalk celery
½ Onion
3 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 packet fresh lasagne sheet
1 packet black beans
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Diced Tomatoes with Garlic & Onion
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 tsp brown sugar
¼ cup water
1 packet Baby Leaves
20 g butter
1 tablespoon (tbsp) plain flour
½ cup milk
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet beef & pork mince

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop celery, onion (see ingredients) and garlic.
• Slice fresh lasagne sheet in half widthways.
• Grate carrot.
• Rinse lentils.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook beef & pork mince, celery, onion and carrot, stirring, until softened, 7-8 minutes.
• Add garlic and garlic & herb seasoning, and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add diced tomatoes, vegetable stock powder, lentils, the brown sugar and water and cook until thickened, 18-20 minutes.
• Season with salt and pepper. Stir through baby leaves until wilted, 1-2 minutes.

• While the filling is cooking, heat a medium frying pan over medium heat. Cook the butter and plain flour, stirring, until a thin paste forms, 1 minute.
• Remove pan from heat, then slowly whisk in the milk. Whisk until smooth. Season to taste.

• Spoon half the filling into a baking dish. Top with a layer of lasagne sheets (lay two sheets alongside each other for 4 people).
• Repeat with the remaining filling and lasagne sheets.

• Top with white sauce and sprinkle over grated Parmesan cheese.
• Bake lasagne until golden, 20-25 minutes.

• Divide beef, pork and lentil hidden veggie lasagne between plates. Enjoy!